{"ts":"2026-06-27T06:26:23.800Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Defining the Architecture**\n\nOkay, I've got a handle on the structural needs. My primary focus is establishing the architecture: a premium admin UI design is essential. I'm thinking about a list of documents displaying both client-wide and project-wide details, with robust filtering by client, project, type, status, owner, and version. I need solid search functionality, and functionality to assign documents to projects.\n\n\n**Refining the UI Narrative**\n\nI'm now refining the UI's core narrative. The document registry's role as a single source of truth for governance and technical schemas is central. Administrators need visual oversight of compliance assets and their validation. The goal is to let admins easily map regulatory documents to active projects, simulating compliance assurance. I am still considering the exact implementation, and need to re-read the page content. I am now looking at creating an internal design plan, and reviewing related content.\n\n\n**Visualizing the Interface**\n\nI'm now honing the interface's visual language. I'm leaning toward a \"Cryptographic Vault\" metaphor, using digital enclave metrics and custom SVG graphics to convey governance. I envision a grid of key stats like \"Total Monitored Documents\" and \"Verified Compliance Enclaves.\" I'm also planning a premium top bar with robust search and filter options. I'm aiming for a dual-mode layout that's high-density on desktops, with responsive card fallbacks for mobile, including an interactive document drawer.\n\n\n**Detailing the Specs**\n\nI'm now detailing technical specs, including cryptographic checksums and verified statuses in a green terminal-style log. Project mapping and document history timelines are under consideration, along with governance status indicators (e.g., ISO-27001). I also plan to add an interactive \"Assign to Project\" modal within the drawer for live state updates.\n\n\n\n**Mapping Data to Concepts**\n\nI'm now mapping real-world data to the document registry concept, using client and project names from existing data. I am thinking through how to model documents for each project and client, and consider the project and client names for document titles. I'm focusing on the technical integration and file-level implementation, specifically, `app/admin/documents/page.tsx`, and how to best use the current data to structure the document registry. I plan to avoid modifying the landing page or core components.\n\n\n**Illustrating with Examples**\n\nNow, I'm working with concrete data examples to structure the document registry. I have three initial data points: a blueprint PDF for Apex Sovereign Group, a SOC2 certificate for Global Retail, and a JSON ruleset for Sovereign Logistics. I can see the client, project, status, owner, version, file details, and governance of each. I'm focusing on their display within the document registry now.\n\n\n\n**Analyzing Data Structure**\n\nI am now closely analyzing the sample document data to flesh out the document registry's structure. I'm focusing on the integration of data from multiple sources. I'm considering the best way to present each document's metadata (SHA-256, governance compliance) and its relation to the assigned project and client.\n\n\n**Structuring the Metadata**\n\nI'm now focusing on structuring the metadata for documents, taking the new examples into account. I've got two new entries: \"Audit Ring (PROJ-202)\" and \"AMD SEV-SNP Attestation Report v1.2\". The fields are coming together. I have all the details, from SHA-256 and file size to status and governance. I am prioritizing a premium presentation. I am also thinking about all of the possible filtering fields, and how they should function.\n\n\n**Designing the Drawer**\n\nI am now designing the document drawer. I've decided to include a modal/dropdown within the drawer for assigning documents to projects, dynamically updating the React state and offering visual confirmation. I'm focusing on metadata display and governance status indicators (ISO-27001, SOC2). I need to check for existing drawer components to reuse.\n\n\n"}}
