{"ts":"2026-06-27T06:26:38.351Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Investigating UI Elements**\n\nI'm currently focused on the `toast` state and how it's used for displaying alerts. My next step is designing an interactive toast alert. I also want to examine the layout, filters, and search functions. Additionally, I'm checking if the `app/admin/documents/page.tsx` file requires any further packages.\n\n\n**Designing Document Page**\n\nI'm now deep in the design of `/app/admin/documents/page.tsx`. I've outlined the necessary states: `searchQuery`, multiple filter states (client, project, type, status, owner, version), a `selectedDoc` state for the slide-over drawer, and states for `documents` and `assigningProjectId`. I'm using `lucide-react` icons and custom structures, and the file uses only import calls.\n\n\n**Defining Document Drawer**\n\nI've been mapping out the document drawer's contents, zeroing in on data presentation. I'm focusing on key sections: the header with title and status, the metadata display with file size and hash, and then the related project section which enables assignment. I'm also planning a governance status section which displays security checks, likely with a dynamic terminal preview.\n\n\n**Defining Mock Data**\n\nI'm now focusing on generating mock data. I'm building out `AVAILABLE_CLIENTS` and `AVAILABLE_PROJECTS` arrays directly within `/app/admin/documents/page.tsx` for testing. I'm keen to ensure these values are realistic and consistent, especially the client-project mappings, to keep them aligned with other parts of the design system. I also want to check for other files that may define client or project options.\n\n\n**Refining Document Details**\n\nI'm now refining the mock document data, particularly considering how to handle unassigned projects. I'm aiming for an initial set of 6-7 documents and I'm defining a structure that includes `project: string` or \"Unassigned\". I'm making sure to define key fields like `id`, `fileSize`, `type`, `status`, `owner`, `version`, `lastUpdated`, `description` and `governanceChecks`, and I'm cross-referencing this structure with the existing fields in `/app/admin/documents/page.tsx`.\n\n\n**Defining Document Hash**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on defining document hashes for my mock data. I've added SHA256 hashes to my mock documents, ensuring data integrity. I've included two sample documents, ensuring the data's structured. This includes titles, file sizes, and types, along with their respective SHA256 fingerprints to represent authentic documents.\n\n\n"}}
