{"ts":"2026-06-27T06:31:28.751Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"5zzisdgp","input":{"summary":"Completed implementation of the high-fidelity Admin Documents Management page at `/admin/documents`.\n\n### Narrative Design Plan Applied\n1. **Narrative/Story**: This page is a Secure Cryptographic Document Registry designed for administrative oversight of compliance, architectural, and governance assets. It displays secure items with active mappings to hardware isolation enclaves and live telemetry streams.\n2. **Visual Metaphor**: Designed with a \"Digital Cryptographic Vault\" theme — premium dark colors (`bg-[#090909]` and `bg-[#050505]/40`), monospace indicators, neon-shaded custom badges, active ping signals, and a custom real-time terminal feed.\n3. **Layout & Multi-Filter Strategy**:\n   - Includes a premium **Oversight Statistics Ribbon** mapping registry totals, active alignment enclaves, ISO-27001 audited rates, and pending mappings.\n   - Features a high-performance **Search & Multi-Filter bar** containing drop-down parameters to filter documents by **client**, **project**, **type** (PDF, JSON, YAML, XML), **governance status** (Verified, Under Review, Action Required, Superseded), **registered owner**, and **revision version**.\n4. **Interactive Document Detail Drawer**: Sliding right-side panel that presents detailed metadata (SHA-256 hash, file size, owner, revision, timestamps), an **interactive project assignment tool** updating bindings live in parent state, an **interactive checklist** for toggling compliance, and a **real-time terminal logging stream** reflecting simulated enclave audits.\n5. **Simulated Secure Action Deck**: Handles secure administrator downloads with temporary connection spinners and browser alert check-ins. Also includes a fully interactive \"Register Asset\" modal to preview adding new blueprints live.\n6. **Mobile Fallback**: Includes custom responsive styling switching from structured grids/tables on desktop to mobile-optimized micro-cards on smaller screens.\n\n### Verification Done\n- Checked syntax and types using `npx tsc --noEmit`, which successfully returned with `0` errors.\n- Verified that all changes are self-contained in `/app/admin/documents/page.tsx` and didn't touch any landing page files or core app files.","verified":true}}}
